evidence.text: Pursuant to Fed. R. Civ. P. 41(a)(1)(A)(ii), and in light of the fact that no binding judgment has been entered in this matter consistent with Federal Rule of Civil Procedure 58, Plaintiffs Jane Doe and Susan Roe and Defendants ... hereby stipulate to the dismissal of this action with prejudice and without attorneys’ fees or costs to either party.
